# Development Rules

## Principles
- **YAGNI**: Don't implement what you don't need yet
- **KISS**: Simplest solution that works
- **DRY**: Extract shared logic, don't copy-paste

## File Standards
- **Naming**: Lowercase Go files (no underscores except `_test.go`); lowercase folder names
- **Size**: Split large files into focused modules
- **Comments**: Only where logic isn't self-evident. No obvious comments

## Code Quality
- Check errors explicitly — don't use `_` for error returns
- No hardcoded secrets, API keys, or credentials
- Validate at system boundaries (handlers, external APIs)
- Prefer early returns over deep nesting
- Don't log and return error at the same time

## Implementation Rules
- Read existing code before modifying — understand patterns first
- Update existing files; don't create "enhanced" copies
- After modifying code, run `go build ./...` or targeted `go test` to verify
- Don't over-engineer: no feature flags or backwards-compat shims for unused code
- Three similar lines > premature abstraction

## Pre-commit
- Run `make lint` and `make tests` before push
- Run `make dep` after dependency edits
- Run `make swagger-load` when HTTP surface or swag annotations change
- Never commit `.env`, credentials, or secrets
